/PG746/XX/PR
Put all your strength into the words/PR
proceeding from letter to letter/PR
with such concentration/PR
that you lose awareness of your bodily self./PR
It will then seem to you that the letters themselves/PR
are flowing into one another./PR
This uniting of the letters is our greatest joy./PR
If joy is felt as two human bodies come together,/PR
how much greater must be the joy/PR
of this union in spirit!/PR
/PR
* */PR
/PR
Do not think that the words of prayer/PR
as you say them/PR
go up to God./PR
It is not the words themselves that ascend;/PR
it is rather the burning desire of your heart/PR
that rises like smoke toward heaven./PR
If your prayer consists only of words and letters,/PR
and does not contain your heartòs desire--/PR
how can it rise up to God?/PR
Nah/±man of Bratzlav (translated by Arthur Green and Barry Holtz)/XX/PR
