/PL747/XX/PR
/KAA Sense of Your Presence/XX/PR
Among our many appetites/PR
There is a craving after God./PR
/PR
Among our many attributes/PR
There is a talent for worshiping God./PR
/PR
Jews who wandered in deserts beneath the stars/PR
Knew their hearts were hungry for God./PR
/PR
Jews who studied in candle-lit ghetto rooms/PR
Thirsted longingly after God./PR
/PR
In tent or hut or slum/PR
Jewish women prayed to God./PR
/PR
But we who are smothered with comfort/PR
Sometimes forget to listen./PR
/PR
Help us, O God, to recognize our need,/PR
To hear the yearning whisper of our hearts./PR
/PR
Help us to seek the silence of the desert/PR
And the thoughtfulness of the house of study./PR
/PR
Bless us, like our ancestors in ancient days/PR
With that most precious gift: a sense of Your presence./PR
/PR
Brush us with the wind of the wings of Your being./PR
Fill us with the awe of Your holiness./PR
We, too, will praise, glorify, and exalt Your name./PR
Ruth Brin (adapted)/XX/PR
