/PG748/XX/PR
/KAUntie/XX/PR
Dear God,/PR
We are bound with very tight knots./PR
They choke off air and stop the blood from pulsating freely./PR
The knots make us like computers with carefully controlled
circuitry./PR
The knots in our brains tie our creativity--our link with You./PR
We follow the knot around in its intricacy--but it remains a
knot./PR
The knots in our hearts keep us from crying and dancing when
we long to--/PR
They tie us to the posts of the fences that separate us from each
other./PR
The knots in our muscles keep our teeth clenched, our jaws
locked, our legs crossed, our shoulders stooped, our backs bent,
our chests from inhaling and exhaling the full sweetness of lifeòs
breath./PR
O, God, untie all our knots!/PR
Sheila Peltz Weinberg/XX/PR
/PR
/KATe Deum/XX/PR
Not because of victories/PR
I sing,/PR
having none,/PR
but for the common sunshine,/PR
the breeze,/PR
the largess of the spring./PR
/PR
Not for victory/PR
but for the dayòs work done/PR
as well as I was able;/PR
not for a seat upon the dais/PR
but at the common table./PR
Charles Reznikoff/XX/PR
