Submit to God, uniquely conscious soul,/PR
And rush to worship God in reverence./PR
Day and night turn toward your eternal source--/PR
Why pursue vanity and emptiness?/PR
Filled with life you resemble the living God/PR
Who is invisible as you are unseen./PR
If your Creator be pure and flawless,/PR
Know that you too are perfect and pure./PR
The Mighty One holds the heavens on one arm,/PR
As you uphold the silent body./PR
My soul, present your songs to your Rock/PR
Who has not placed your form in the dust./PR
My limbs, praise your Rock continuously/PR
The one whose name every soul does praise./PR
Solomon ibn Gabirol (translated by Reena Spicehandler)/XX/PR
